Wash and dry produce.

Trim and roughly chop @scallions{2}. Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}. Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Dice @tomato{1}. Drain and rinse @black beans{1%can}.

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine scallions, 2 TBSP @olive oil{2%tablespoon}, and 1 tsp @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon} (you'll use more in the next step). Stir in a pinch of garlic and a squeeze of lime juice to taste. Season generously with salt and @pepper{}. Taste and add more garlic and lime juice as needed.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. Add tomato and remaining garlic; cook, stirring, until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add beans, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, 1/2 cup water (1/3 cup for 4 servings), 1 tsp Southwest spice blend (1 TBSP for 4), salt, and pepper. (You'll use the rest of the Southwest spice blend in the next step.) Simmer until thickened, ~{5-10%minutes}.

Turn off heat; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Season with salt and pepper. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, pat @beef tenderloin steak{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season with remaining Southwest spice blend, salt, and pepper.

> Swap in chicken or beef for pork. Cook chicken until browned and cooked through, 3-5 minutes per side, or cook beef to desired doneness, 4-7 minutes per side.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat. Add beef and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

Transfer to a #cutting board{}.

While beef cooks, in a second small bowl, combine @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}, half the lime zest, a squeeze of lime juice, and a big pinch of salt. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon}, remaining lime zest, a squeeze of lime juice, salt, and pepper.

Once cool enough to handle, slice beef crosswise.

> Once cool enough to handle, thinly slice chicken or beef against the grain.

Divide rice and beef between plates. Top rice with bean mixture and crema. Top beef with salsa. Cut any remaining lime into smaller wedges and serve on the side.

> Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.